Sentencas: The electrical conductivity and electrochemical performance of a La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-delta (LSC) cathode produced by a modified citrate-EDTA sol-gel method assisted with activated carbon are characterized for a proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell (H+ -SOFC) application at intermediate temperature.
Titulo: Electrical and electrochemical characteristics of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ cathode materials synthesized by a modified citrate-EDTA sol-gel method assisted with activated carbon for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: Thermogravimetric analysis revealed that the decomposition of the unrequired intermediate compounds in the precalcined powder was completed at 800 A degrees C. A single LSC perovskite phase was formed at a calcination temperature of 900 A degrees C, as confirmed by X-ray diffraction analysis.
Titulo: Electrical and electrochemical characteristics of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ cathode materials synthesized by a modified citrate-EDTA sol-gel method assisted with activated carbon for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: The particle size, crystallite size, and BET-specific surface area of the powder are 219-221 nm, 18 nm, and 9.87 m(2) g(-1), respectively.
Titulo: Electrical and electrochemical characteristics of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ cathode materials synthesized by a modified citrate-EDTA sol-gel method assisted with activated carbon for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: The high index value of the extent of agglomeration (5.53) showed that the powder was barely agglomerated.
Titulo: Electrical and electrochemical characteristics of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ cathode materials synthesized by a modified citrate-EDTA sol-gel method assisted with activated carbon for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: Bulk LSC sintered at 1200 A degrees C for 2 h showed the highest direct-current electrical conductivity (sigma (d.c)) compared to that of bulk LSC sintered at 1000 A degrees C and 1100 A degrees C.
Titulo: Electrical and electrochemical characteristics of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ cathode materials synthesized by a modified citrate-EDTA sol-gel method assisted with activated carbon for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: The value of sigma (d.c) was affected by the density and porosity of the sintered samples.
Titulo: Electrical and electrochemical characteristics of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ cathode materials synthesized by a modified citrate-EDTA sol-gel method assisted with activated carbon for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell application

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) of screen-printed LSC working on a proton conductor of BaCe0.54Zr0.36Y0.1O2.95 (BCZY) decreased from 5.0 Omega cm(2)-0.06 Omega cm(2) as the temperature increased from 500 A degrees C to 800 A degrees C with an activation energy of 1.079 eV. Overall, in this work, the LSC material produced with the aid of activated carbon meet the requirements for the application as a cathode in an intermediate temperature H+-SOFC.
Titulo: Electrical and electrochemical characteristics of La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ cathode materials synthesized by a modified citrate-EDTA sol-gel method assisted with activated carbon for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cell application
